Thirteen ODM defectors are set to appear before the party's National Disciplinary Committee at Intercontinental Hotel on October 14.The defectors were to face the party s disciplinary committee on Friday but were represented by their lawyer Kioko Kilukumi.Kilukumi sought the adjournment of the proceedings to allow affected members to appear in person at a neutral venue.He addressed journalist after a meeting with the ODM council on Friday,ODM threatened to kick out the defectors in what might trigger unprecedented by-elections with only 10 months to the 2017 general election.They include Marsabit Governor Ukur Yatani, his Kwale counterpart Salim Mvurya and Kwale woman representative Zainab Chidzuga.Others are Kisii Deputy Governor Joash Maangi, Mathare MP Steven Kariuki, Gideon Mung aro (Kilifi), Isaac Mwaura (Nominated) and James Rege (Karachuonyo).But some of the targeted MPs have accused ODM of dishonesty in the purge, saying Raila and the Orange party have also been receiving defectors.Read: ODM disciplinary committee summons defectors